        <briefdescription>
<para>Shakes the inputted camera for a specified amount of time with a certain intensity following an animation curve. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>For best results, don&apos;t move the camera directly via any other scripts. Camera can also be any transform, so you can shake other objects with these</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>camera</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Camera to apply screenshake to, default is Camera.main</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>intensity</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A multiplier for more screenshake</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>duration</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>How many seconds the screenshake lasts for</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>curve</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Curve used to apply screenshake</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>useRealtime</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If true, will use Time.unscaledDeltatime, instead of Time.deltaTime</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
